children.text: The concrete slab has been incorrectly boxed and poured which has resulted in the bottom plate of the wall being cut along the entire length of the load-bearing wall.

The relevant Australian Standard AS 1684 Residential Timber-Framed Construction, clause 6.2.1.4 Notching, Trenching and Holes in Studs and Plates only allows cutting and drilling of plates up to 25mm in the centre third. There is no allowance for ripping the plate down along the length of the wall.
The incorrectly sized concrete slab should be trimmed back under the supervision of the engineer, and the wall bottom plate replaced with the correct size member to comply with the above allowance.
